article.headline: E. Michigan 63, Ohio 56
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Jarred Axon scored 18 points and Carlos Medlock added 13 and five assists Wednesday to help Eastern Michigan stop a three-game losing streak with a 63-56 victory over Ohio. Justin Orr, Leon Williams and Bubba Walther had nine points apiece for the Bobcats (15-7, 6-3 Mid-American), who saw a five-game winning streak end. Ohio's 17-for-49 performance (35 percent) from the field was its worst in a conference game this season. Jesse Bunkley scored five of his 12 points during a 13-2 run early in the second half that gave the Eagles (8-13, 4-5) a cushion they never lost. Ohio never got closer than six points the rest of the game. The Eagles outscored Ohio 8-3 in the final four minutes of the first half and led 26-21 at intermission.
